 Step 1 - Create new virtual machine in VMware Workstation 
- Click on Create new virtual machine, Select Typical and Click Next
- Select Installer Disc Image file and Click on Browse (Find the VMvisor iso file and select it) then Click Next 
- Give the virtual machine a name and Click Next
- Select Number of Processors and set ram as 16gb
- Select Network Address Translation and select Scsi then click next
- Select Split virtual disk into multiple files and Click Next 
- click finish and the VM is created
- Click on Power ON this virtual machine
- After powering on ESXi will start installing
- Press Enter and Press F11  to Accept and Continue 
- Press Enter until root password. after setting root password press Enter
- Press F11 to Install ESXi then Press Enter to Reboot
- In VMware Workstation Click on Power on this Virtual Machine 
- To configure SSH press F2 and enter your password then Press Enter
- In  System Customization Select Troubleshooting Options and Press Enter 
- Within Troubleshooting Options Select Enable SSH and Press Enter 
-  Press Esc twice to save and exit from settings 

Step 2 - Configuring ESXi Host Client 
- Power On the virtual machine and Copy the IP Address of the server and Paste it into your Web Browser 
- ESXi Host Client Click -> Storage -> Datastore Browser  -> Create Directory -> Enter Name 
- After the new directory is created Click on Windows 7 and Select the Upload option 
- in Host Directory find the iso file and Open. after it opens and loads click Close
- Host Client Dashboard -> Virtual Machines ->Create / Register a new VM 
- Enter a Name for the virtual machine and edit the following 
Compatibility = default value 
Select Guest OS Family = Windows 
Select Guest OS Version = Microsoft Windows 7 (64-bit) and Click Next
Select the Standard datastore and Click Next
Keep CPU at 1 core 
Memory at 2048 MB 
Hard Disk at 8 GB 
Disk Provisioning as Thin provisioned 
CD/DVD Drive 1
The remaining can have their default value
- Select Power on and Click Next then Finish
- Click on the virtual machine -> Edit -> CD/DVD Drive 1 -> Connect -> Save -> Power on

Step 3 - Install VMware Tools -
- Select Actions -> Guest OS -> Install VMware Tools
	
Step 4 - Copy Files to Desktop
- Drag drop a desired file to the VM's Desktop after installing VMWare Too 



